& \frac{\omega}{c} = k_{z} = \sqrt{\frac{\alpha^{2}}{\varepsilon_{1}} - \frac{\alpha^{2}}{\widetilde{\varepsilon}_{2}}}. \\
3. & \text{For surface plasmon polaritons to propagate without reflection, } k_{z} \text{ must be purely imaginary: }
& \frac{\omega}{c} = k_{z} = \mathrm{i}k_{z}' \text{ where } k_{z}' \text{ is real.} \\
4. & \text{Substitute } k_{z} = \mathrm{i}k_{z}' \text{ into the dispersion relation and separate real and imaginary parts:}
& \frac{\omega}{c} = \mathrm{i}k_{z}', \text{ and }\frac{\alpha^{2}}{\varepsilon_{1}} = \frac{\alpha^{2}}{\widetilde{\varepsilon}_{2}}. \\
5. & \text{Solve for }\alpha: \alpha = \frac{\omega}{c}\sqrt{\varepsilon_{1}\widetilde{\varepsilon}_{2}}. \\
6. & \text{The wavelength }\lambda \text{ is given by }\lambda = \frac{2\pi}{\alpha} = \frac{2\pi c}{\omega}\sqrt{\frac{1}{\varepsilon_{1}\widetilde{\varepsilon}_{2}}}. \\
